2015-11-03 SEATTLE, Nov.3, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ -- Recently selected VegNews Company of the Year, Field Roast Grain Meat Co. is pleased to introduce two new elegant centerpieces this holiday season. These exciting new roasts are expected to raise the bar for vegan and vegetarian options with the addition of new ingredients and flavors. This November, Field Roast introduces its new evolution of the Celebration Roast with Traditional Bread Stuffing and Porcini Mushroom Gravy. The Smokey Forager's Roast, inspired by the Northwest, is stuffed with foraged chanterelle mushrooms and wild huckleberries  complete with a Pineapple Mustard Glaze.  The long-time favorite Hazelnut Cranberry Roast en Croute is packed with cranberries, apples and crystalized ginger  surrounded by hazelnut-infused grain meat and a savory puff pastry. The Classic Celebration Roast remains a vegetarian staple, with its sausage stuffing, butternut squash, mushrooms and rubbed sage finish. About Field Roast Grain Meat CompanyFounded in 1997 and selected as VegNews 2015 Company of the Year, Field Roast creates artisan vegan meats and cheeses made with real ingredients. Field Roast can be found in over 2,000 retail stores and 500 restaurant menus nationwide and beyond. For more information, visit fieldroast.com. Join the conversation on Facebook and Twitter. For press inquiries, please contact: Kiley Simmons, kiley.simmons@fieldroast.com, 206-762-5961 Photo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151103/283388  To view the original version on PR Newswire, visit:http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/field-roast-brings-unprecedented-flavor-to-the-table-with-new-holiday-roasts-300171517.html SOURCE  The Field Roast Grain Meat Company 